                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d553">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 822.124/283.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-06-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 26, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Americans should not be excluded from work of sanitation, especially after
                    Ecuador invited the Isthmian Canal Commission to make report on the work which
                    Colonel Gorgas made. Use your best efforts to secure for Americans opportunity
                    to obtain contract. Give names of American firms bidding.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
